				just in my PC) with HTML and notepad!. It was really fun. I showed it to
				all my friends and family.
			</p>
		</Section>
	</main>

	<style lang="scss">
		.hero {
			display: flex;
			flex-direction: column;
			height: 80vh;
			align-items: center;
			background-color: var(--c-background);
			justify-content: space-around;

			@media (min-width: 600px) {
				height: 100vh;
			}
			@media (min-width: 800px) {
				flex-direction: row;
				justify-content: space-between;
			}
		}
		.right {
			background-repeat: no-repeat;
			background-size: cover;
			overflow: hidden;

			@media (min-width: 800px) {
				background-image: url(/assets/shape.svg);
				height: 100%;
				display: flex;
				justify-content: center;
				align-items: center;
			}
		}

		.main-img {
			width: 25rem;

			@media (min-width: 600px) {
				width: 40rem;
				animation: imgTransition 2s;
			}
			@media (min-width: 800px) {
				width: 45rem;
			}
			@media (min-width: 1100px) {
				width: 60rem;
			}
		}

		@keyframes imgTransition {
			0% {
				transform: translateX(30rem);
				opacity: 0;
			}

			50% {
				transform: translateX(-7rem);
				opacity: 0.7;
			}

			100% {
				transform: translateX(0rem);
				opacity: 1;
			}
		}

		.left {
			display: flex;
			align-items: center;
			padding: 1rem;
			margin-top: 10rem;

			@media (min-width: 800px) {
				margin-top: 0;
				padding-left: 1rem;
			}
			@media (min-width: 1000px) {
				padding-left: 4rem;
			}
		}
		.title {
			font-weight: 900;
		}

		.name {
			font-size: 3rem;
			display: block;
			line-height: 1;
			text-align: center;

			@media (min-width: 600px) {
				font-size: 4.5rem;
			}

			@media (min-width: 800px) {
				width: 2rem;
				font-size: 5rem;
				text-align: left;
			}

			@media (min-width: 1100px) {
				font-size: 6.5rem;
			}
		}

		.subtitle {
			font-size: 2rem;
			margin-bottom: 1rem;
			display: block;
			font-weight: 400;
			letter-spacing: -0.0625em;

			@media (min-width: 600px) {
				font-size: 3rem;
			}
		}
	</style>
</Overall>
